[{"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-11T17:17:01+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A person pets the top of Casio\u2019s Moflin robotic pet.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/SmgeJQNxfM56EYKahEVuNXgRb1Y=/0x1:1275x851/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73648026/moflin1.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Unlike Sony\u2019s robotic dog, Aibo, Casio\u2019s Moflin can\u2019t run away on its own.</em> | Image: Casio</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"rfha9x\">Casio has opened preorders for its <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.casio.com%2Fjp%2Fmoflin%2F&amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2024%2F10%2F11%2F24268063%2Fcasio-robot-pet-moflin\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">robotic pet called Moflin</a> that looks like a cross between a hamster and <em>Star Trek</em>\u2019s Tribbles. Unlike <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2018/1/11/16876086/sony-aibo-hands-on-video-ces-2018\">Sony\u2019s robot dog Aibo</a> that can follow you around, Moflin is de", "id": 1309945, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/11/24268063/casio-robot-pet-moflin", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Casio made a furry robot designed to cuddle and calm you down", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-11T16:10:27+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of a computer screen with a blue exclamation point on it and an error box.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/2ZqbUMlsZTx2WC1orcCt_Trb3cA=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73647883/akrales_220309_4977_0232.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Amelia Holowaty Krales / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"OPtw5j\">The Internet Archive will come back within \u201cdays\u201d following a cyberattack that brought down the organization\u2019s vast digital library and the Wayback Machine, according to an <a href=\"https://x.com/brewster_kahle/status/1844790609573277792\">update from founder Brewster Kahle</a>. It\u2019s been struggling due to a <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/9/24266419/internet-archive-ddos-attack-pop-up-message\">data breach and DDoS attack</a> earlier this week that revealed the email addresses, screen names, password change timestamps, and other information associated with more than 31 million", "id": 1309530, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/11/24268040/internet-archive-data-breach-outage-hacked", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The Internet Archive is still down but will return in \u2018days, not weeks\u2019", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-11T15:58:29+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"The Steam brand logo against a blue and black backdrop\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/QHkBLTkcssT4RGkZ8lolaaZuOA8=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73647852/STK138_Stream_Kradtke_02.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"MBCku1\">Valve is now explicitly disclosing that you don\u2019t own the games you buy from its Steam online store. The company has added a note on the payment checkout screen stating that \u201ca purchase of a digital product grants a license for the product on Steam,\u201d <a href=\"https://www.engadget.com/gaming/steam-now-tells-gamers-up-front-that-theyre-buying-a-license-not-a-game-085106522.html?guccounter=1\">as reported earlier by <em>Engadget</em></a>.</p>\n<p id=\"O4dLmt\">We confirmed the message appears in the Steam desktop app, but we haven\u2019t seen it in the mobile app yet. Some Steam users noticed the disclosure go live earlier this week and <a href=\"https://ww", "id": 1309531, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/11/24267864/steam-buy-purchase-license-digital-storefront", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Steam now says the \u2018game\u2019 you\u2019re buying is really just a license    ", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-11T15:12:14+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Vector illustration of the Xbox logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/qMJXEoLug4e3cm1m6J5tvDykzLc=/20x0:2021x1334/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73647766/STK048_XBOX_C.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"lwbH8K\">Microsoft is planning to support the streaming of Xbox game libraries next month. Sources familiar with Microsoft\u2019s plans tell <em>The Verge</em> that the company is getting ready to test the ability to stream games that you own that aren\u2019t part of the existing Xbox Game Pass library.</p>\n<p id=\"yQPBtg\">As part of a long-running project known as Project Lapland inside of Microsoft, the software giant has been readying its Xbox Cloud Gaming servers to be able to support streaming thousands of games. I\u2019m told Microsoft will first test its new Xbox Cloud Gaming streaming capabilities with Xbox Insiders in November, before expanding them to more Xbox users and more ga", "id": 1308592, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/11/24268038/xbox-cloud-gaming-project-lapland-game-library", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Xbox Cloud Gaming will let you stream your own games in November ", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-11T14:44:03+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo of Panic\u2019s Cabel Sasser onstage at XOXO 2024.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/7uPtxGxNycopAiG_09u7TwG8CqA=/300x0:1920x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73647690/videoframe_298102.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Panic\u2019s Cabel Sasser at XOXO 2024.</em> | Image: XOXO Fest</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"NY2TmY\">I know there\u2019s a lot to do on the internet, but you really should stop what you\u2019re doing and watch <a href=\"https://youtu.be/Df_K7pIsfvg?feature=shared\">this 19-minute talk</a> about a bespoke mural that once lived inside a McDonald\u2019s.</p>\n<p id=\"nBL9qr\">The talk, given by Cabel Sasser of Panic at XOXO Fest 2024, was filled with silliness and deep dives down unexpected rabbit holes. (I\u2019d expect nothing less from the founder of Panic, the company behind whimsical things like <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23025390/playdate-handheld-portable-gaming-console-review\">the Playdate handheld</a> and <a href=\"h", "id": 1308593, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/11/24230990/mcdonalds-bespoke-painting-cabel-sasser-wes-cook-xoxo-2024", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "You must watch this amazing presentation about a bespoke McDonald\u2019s mural", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-11T13:38:57+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Imgur\u2019s homepage.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/gsH5NzugPfcr4cuQUREQG6vBEik=/0x0:750x500/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73647568/3_Homepage.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Imgur</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"T0ES21\">Memes on the image-hosting service Imgur \u201ccontaining references to adult humor\u201d will no longer be considered mature, the company announced <a href=\"https://imgur.com/gallery/greetings-imgurians-q4-2024-update-KBefaiM\">in a post</a> addressing changes to its content moderation policies. </p>\n<p id=\"74mITz\">Imgur has been an important part of meme history, with its creator making the service <a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/reddit.com/comments/7zlyd/my_gift_to_reddit_i_created_an_image_hosting/\">in 2009 as a \u201cgift to Reddit.\u201d</a> At that time, most platforms didn\u2019t host their own images, so you had to upload them instead on third-party platforms. I remember seeing Imgur a lot on the Something Awful fo", "id": 1308594, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/11/24267304/imgur-less-strict-memes-adult-humor-content-moderation-mature", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Imgur is going to be less strict about memes with adult humor", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-11T13:36:34+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"An image showing the Threads logo\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/s0MhXR0alG1OncdtgGawXkv61gM=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73647560/STK156_Instagram_threads_1.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"gmjroU\">Head of Instagram Adam Mosseri is acknowledging recent mistakes in Meta\u2019s moderation processes on Threads and Instagram. For example, Meta unexpectedly deleted my account this week because it thought I was underage, the company locked my colleague\u2019s account because she joked about dying in a heatwave, and others have seen their posts disappear <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/9/24266096/instagram-threads-moderation-account-post-deleted-limited\">with no clear reason why</a>. \u201cThreads Moderation Failures\u201d <a href=\"https://www.threads.net/search?q=Threads%20Moderation%20Failures\">has been trending this week</a> \u2014 putting more pressure on Meta\u2019s moder", "id": 1308595, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/11/24267898/mosseri-acknowledges-mistakes-threads-instagram-broken-moderation", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Adam Mosseri acknowledges \u2018mistakes\u2019 in Threads\u2019 broken moderation", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-11T13:14:15+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Thrustmaster\u2019s T598 racing wheel next to its Raceline Pedals LTE.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/VNtxGa25uiZIBaWVfuCmgV9_ABs=/0x0:934x623/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73647510/thrustmaster2.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The Thrustmaster T598 features a Direct Axial Drive powered by an axial flux electric motor.</em> | Image: Thrustmaster</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"qNkfsm\">Thrustmaster has announced a new <a href=\"https://www.thrustmaster.com/en-us/products/t598/\">steering wheel base</a> that makes the company\u2019s direct drive technology available on consoles for the first time. It also introduces a new electric motor design \u2014 already in use on high-end hybrid sports cars like the <a href=\"https://www.ferrari.com/en-EN/auto/sf90-stradale\">Ferrari SF90</a> \u2014 to the world of sim racing, improving realism while also shrinking the hardware.</p>\n<p id=\"FVnMKN\">The Thrustmaster T598 can be preordered today for $499.99", "id": 1308596, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/11/24267818/thrustmaster-racing-sim-wheel-t598-sony-playstation-direct-axial-drive", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Thrustmaster brings direct drive steering wheels to console racing sims", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-11T13:11:39+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"An image from MKBHD\u2019s Panels video.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/XDjDxcQ_y3GR6QpSGvPkwW8w3mw=/74x0:1994x1280/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73647509/videoframe_19176__1_.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: MKBHD</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"KrxegB\">Marques Brownlee published <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=65ciAONXv0M\">a video on Friday</a> addressing the criticisms around <a href=\"https://panels.art/\">Panels</a>, his new wallpaper app, saying that he and the team \u201cfailed on the price front\u201d at launch. The app received <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/24/24253023/mkbhd-panels-wallpaper-app-response-criticism\">an outpour of criticism</a> from fans, both on the MKBHD YouTube channel and across social platforms. Discussing the app, Brownlee admitted it needed work. \u201cIf I was reviewing this app, I would not have been very nice,\u201d he said.</p>\n<p id=\"qoQ1uy\">One of the primary criticisms of the app was ", "id": 1308597, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/11/24267900/marques-brownlee-mkbhd-price-panels-wallpaper-app", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Marques Brownlee says \u2018we failed on the price\u2019 with Panels ", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-11T12:45:19+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Vector collage of the X logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/MhmZ1zN8ekySHTCPgryTal_Kj1A=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73647426/STK160_X_TWITTER_2__B.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"GDsI42\">X is dropping claims against Unilever in <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/6/24214536/x-elon-musk-antitrust-lawsuit-advertisers-boycott\">its lawsuit</a> that accuses advertisers and brands of participating in an \u201cillegal boycott\u201d of the company. The claims against Unilever, which owns household names like Dove and Hellmann\u2019s, <a href=\"https://storage.courtlistener.com/recap/gov.uscourts.txnd.393003/gov.uscourts.txnd.393003.60.0.pdf\">were dismissed today</a>.</p>\n<p id=\"G9v4gI\">Last fall, <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/20/23970274/x-elon-musk-media-matters-lawsuit-nazi-ads-filed\">X also sued the nonprofit Media Matters for America</a> in an effort to sile", "id": 1308598, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/11/24267784/x-unilever-lawsuit-advertiser-boycott-garm-elon-musk", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "X drops Unilever from its \u2018advertiser boycott\u2019 lawsuit", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-11T12:26:44+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo of Apple\u2019s USB SuperDrive.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Ywn7BhkK9uqqNYoC38-lwOC3CI8=/0x148:2000x1481/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73647385/MD564.0.jpeg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Apple</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"mj4Rxy\">Apple\u2019s USB SuperDrive is showing up in Apple\u2019s online stores as \u201csold out or unavailable in all countries,\u201d <a href=\"https://www.macrumors.com/2024/10/11/apple-quietly-discontinues-16-year-old-accessory/\"><em>MacRumors</em> reports</a>, which could indicate that Apple has discontinued the CD / DVD player. </p>\n<p id=\"8QZCFw\">It\u2019s not a huge surprise that Apple might be done with the SuperDrive. The product first launched with the original MacBook Air, which didn\u2019t have an optical drive, in 2008, so it\u2019s quite old. The SuperDrive was shown as \u201csold out\u201d online on Apple\u2019s US online store <a href=\"https://9to5mac.com/2024/08/05/apple-superdrive-discontinued/\">earlier this year</a>. And", "id": 1308599, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/11/24267842/apple-usb-superdrive-discontinued", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Apple\u2019s USB SuperDrive might be gone for good", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-11T11:08:55+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Tesla Cybercab\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/3R4O8eJdbcdTnLplnYGKC11DYj4=/0x0:7680x5120/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73647231/Robotaxi_89.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Tesla</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>Elon Musk promised a brighter future, but believing him requires an enormous leap of faith. </p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/11/24267727/tesla-cybercab-unanswered-questions-fsd-safety-liability\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>\n\n", "id": 1308600, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/11/24267727/tesla-cybercab-unanswered-questions-fsd-safety-liability", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The Tesla Cybercab is a cool-looking prototype that needed to be much more than that", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-11T10:26:42+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"iPhone on a colorful illustrated background showing people using iPhones\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Y_32eLrRAOwqlGGeUPvny5iTpBI=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73647137/HT015_S_Haddad_ios_iphone_apps.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Samar Haddad / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"L2FHg8\">Having to hand your iPhone over to someone can be a fairly common occurrence. Maybe your little nephew wants to play a game or your friend wants to check out the photos from your <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/5/23/23734821/photoshop-generative-ai-fill-tool-adobe\">last vacation</a>. Whatever the reason, no matter how much you trust that person, there are probably parts of your phone that you\u2019d rather they didn\u2019t see (even accidentally).</p>\n<p id=\"8k9xFg\">That\u2019s where the new Face ID lock in iOS 18 comes in: you can now get your iPhone to ask for biometric authentication whenever a particu", "id": 1307447, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24267102/iphone-ios-18-lock-app-how-to", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "How to lock any app with Face ID on an iPhone using iOS 18", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-11T10:25:25+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"silver two-door muscle car on a track\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/tkW7Wdxr4zJjK_uSuk3copQxaGo=/0x0:3000x2000/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73647135/DG024_017CH.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>2024 Dodge Charger Daytona Scat Pack.</em> | Image: Stellantis</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"OQ3EIV\">Stellantis is shaking up its leadership. The company <a href=\"https://media.stellantisnorthamerica.com/newsrelease.do?id=26318&amp;mid=1\">announced today</a> that CEO Carlos Tavares will retire at the end of his contract in 2026, and a host of other executives are being around being shuffled around immediately. The changes come as Stellantis struggles to manage its US auto business, which includes Chrysler, Jeep, Dodge, and Ram. The company is actively looking for Tavares\u2019 successor.</p>\n<p id=\"Yh5KUZ\">On his way out, the executive shakeup includes replacing the current CFO, Natalie Knight, and North American COO, Carlos Zar", "id": 1307448, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/11/24267706/stellantis-ceo-carlos-tavares-retiring-executive-changes", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Stellantis\u2019 CEO promises to leave in 2026 after mostly making a mess of things", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-11T09:25:27+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"An image showing the aftermath of Hurricane Helene in Spruce Pine, NC\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/boXhYMMUvIdygwZ_wFlApLVeaGo=/630x0:7434x4536/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73646951/2176989044.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Spruce Pine, North Carolina, was hit with major flooding and power outages.</em> | Photo by Steve Exum / Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"TD5fn4\">Sibelco, one of the companies mining high-purity quartz in Spruce Pine, North Carolina, has resumed operations. <a href=\"https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20241010766052/en/Sibelco-Restarts-Production-and-Customer-Shipments-at-Spruce-Pine-Following-Hurricane-Helene\">In an update on Thursday</a>, the company said that production and shipments of the quartz, which is crucial to the chipmaking process, are \u201cprogressively ramping up to full capacity.\u201d</p>\n<p id=\"mAf1A2\">After Hurricane Helene caused <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024", "id": 1307449, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/11/24267697/north-carolina-quartz-sibelco-resumes-operations-hurricane-helene", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Crucial North Carolina quartz mine is up and running following Hurricane Helene", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-11T08:59:21+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"An illustration of a gavel on a Google logo, over the Vergecast illustration.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/szB2huxQfoXdbtFmcdaIM-FWr_A=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73646856/VRG_VST_101124_Site.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Alex Parkin / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"A9udTz\">Lawsuits take a long time, and so there\u2019s no good reason to believe that Google as we know it will be gone anytime soon. But as the antitrust fight against the company continues, and Google\u2019s losses mount, it\u2019s also starting to seem like Google as we know also won\u2019t be around forever. In one case, <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/policy/2024/10/7/24243316/epic-google-permanent-injunction-ruling-third-party-stores\">the Play Store is being opened up</a>; in another, the government says it might try to <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/8/24265832/google-search-antitrust-remedies-framework-android-