e": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "How SpaceX became the MyPillow of government contractors", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-11T08:30:00+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/GwC10eWbiBxQtkn65zFZiwjLZ5w=/0x209:5000x3542/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73646821/LYNKCO_02_Exterior_04_Hires_D8d8a9.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The 02 is Lynk &amp; Co\u2019s first all-electric car.</em> | Image: Lynk &amp; Co</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"PJiVRJ\">Lynk &amp; Co just launched the 02, the company\u2019s first fully-electric vehicle that\u2019s designed from the ground up to be shared with family, friends, or anyone willing to pay for the privilege. The EV is interesting, but not nearly as interesting as Lynk &amp; Co\u2019s unique approach to car ownership.</p>\n<p id=\"ovICE1\">Once you buy, lease, or subscribe to a 02 you can become a \u201clender,\u201d in Lynk &amp; Co parlance, to set the price and conditions for sharing. In Amsterdam, a quick browse through the Lynk &amp; Co app shows several of its <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/22557411/lynk-co-01-cheaper-as-you-share-volvo-geely-pri", "id": 1307036, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/11/24267648/lynk-and-co-02-ev-sharing-price-specs", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Lynk & Co\u2019s first EV is meant to be shared to lower its price", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-11T08:12:30+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A screenshot of a pinned post on Bluesky.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/TbO-DqdHrSQ3YHD14ZZ9RlCKK3o=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73646795/Bluesky_pinned_posts.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The Bluesky app will now let users pin posts to the top of their profiles.</em> | Image: Bluesky</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"L9anso\">Bluesky will now let you pin posts, apply language filters, and customize fonts and text sizes. The decentralized short posting platform announced <a href=\"https://www.threads.net/@bluesky_social/post/DA9hnXQyrdP\">these and other new features</a> via the Threads account it <a href=\"https://www.threads.net/@bluesky_social/post/DA6anHYSrUE?xmt=AQGzoaw0C0LcoPsGymacxMV4gNfTqic5fNcGwEtNvOioIA\">created yesterday</a>, seizing the chance to promote its superiority \u2014 \u201c<a href=\"https://www.threads.net/@bluesky_social/post/DA82FsEvg7T?xmt=AQGzqWbsZd1lJvBIWWaXbAAC4p2KV_YrPg_QPqL5vSGpOg\">we\u2019", "id": 1307038, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/11/24267678/bluesky-app-update-pinned-posts-font-size-threads-pitch", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Bluesky pitches new features at disgruntled Threads users", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-11T08:00:00+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"M3 Max MacBook Pro 16 next to an M3 MacBook Pro 14 in front of boxy geometric bookshelves\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/DlpmafQOd-lx8h9kiwvhV7p1SUA=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73646710/236896_MacBook_Pro_14_and_16_M3_AKrales_0062.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The M3 Pro generation of MacBook Pros arrived about one year ago in October 2023.</em> | Photo by Amelia Holowaty Krales / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"Spzc8k\">Another round of Apple devices is about to arrive. After launching the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24247479/apple-iphone-16-plus-review-camera-control-screen-battery\">iPhone 16</a> lineup, new <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24246464/apple-watch-series-10-review-smartwatch-wearables\">Apple Watches</a>, and the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24245570/apple-airpods-4-review\">AirPods 4</a> in September, Apple appears to be gearing up to introduce updated Macs and i", "id": 1306551, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/11/24253972/apple-event-october-macbook-pro-air-rumors-date-time-livestream-watch-how-to", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "What to expect from Apple\u2019s next Mac and iPad announcements", "vote": 0}]